President Muhammadu Buhari yesterday held a special consultation with Service Chiefs at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. This is coming 24 hours after the president had pledged that, in the coming weeks, Nigerians would witness an aggressive campaign to rout Boko Haram once and for all. This follows the recent upsurge in Boko Haram attacks. Present at the meeting were the chief of defence staff, General Gabriel Olonisakin; chief of army staff; Lt.-Gen Tukur Buratai; chief of air staff, Air Marshal Sadique Abubakar; chief of naval staff, Vice Admiral Ibok-Ete Ekwe Ibas, and Inspector General of Police, Mohammed Adamu. However, the National Security Adviser (NSA), Major-General Babagana Monguno (rtd)  was conspicuously absent from the meeting . The service chiefs did not brief State House correspondents after the meeting.